<subSubSection pageId="77" pageNumber="78" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="77.[151,1437,1627,1942]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,436,1627,1654]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Recognition characters:</emphasis>
Blackish species; length 
<quantity box="[717,812,1627,1654]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" unit="mm" value="6.0" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="5.0">5–7 mm</quantity>
; mystax white; thorax gray pollinose, pilosity less dense than preceding setae on abdominal segment 1 only; wings brown; legs black, setae and bristles white on femora and tibiae, black on tarsi.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="77.[151,1437,1627,1942]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,355,1735,1762]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Distribution:</emphasis>
PLATTE: 
<quantity box="[482,555,1735,1761]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.4" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" unit="km" value="64.0">64 km</quantity>
NE of Laramie, 
<date box="[751,900,1735,1762]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" value="1937-07-13">13 July 1937</date>
(
<collectionCode box="[917,1032,1736,1762]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">RHB-UK</collectionCode>
): Laramie Peak, Laramie Mtns.; 
<date pageId="77" pageNumber="78" value="1964-07-17">17 July 1964</date>
(
<collectionCode box="[276,327,1772,1798]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">RJL</collectionCode>
, 
<collectionCode box="[338,397,1772,1798]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">FRH</collectionCode>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="77.[151,1437,1627,1942]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,300,1807,1834]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Habitat:</emphasis>
Grama-needlegrass-wheatgrass grassland vegetation 
<typeStatus box="[922,974,1808,1834]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">type</typeStatus>
. Local population occurred in stand of mountain mahogany on edge of clearing, on mountainside.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="77.[151,1437,1627,1942]" box="[199,1436,1879,1906]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,316,1880,1906]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Ethology:</emphasis>
Rests on and forages from tips of dead branches of mountain mahogany 0.6– 
<quantity box="[1189,1227,1879,1906]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" unit="m" value="1.0">1 m</quantity>
above the ground.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="77.[151,1437,1627,1942]" box="[199,422,1915,1942]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,264,1916,1942]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Prey:</emphasis>
None known.
</paragraph>
